This paper discusses the regulation of highly automated robot ecologies, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses decision support and adaptive autonomy, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The user studies mentioned in the paper involve interactions between people and robots, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the societal impact of regulating HARE, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA).
